external_knowledge:
API endpoints are URLs that an application uses to interact with an API; 
In this context, the 'version hierarchy' refers to how different versions of the API endpoints are related to one another; 
Usage statistics include total accesses, average response time, and total errors encountered by an endpoint; 
Documentation refers to the most recent documentation available for an endpoint.

- 'roads to API success' refers to API endpoints that return a successful HTTP status code (200);
- 'require a passport' means the endpoints require authentication;
- 'are not closed' means the endpoints are not deprecated;
- 'fastest to the slowest roads' refers to sorting the endpoints by their average response time in ascending order.

